description:
The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI EMU Index composed of large- and mid-capitalization equities from developed market countries that use the euro as their official currency.
 The fund generally invests at least 95% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index and in depositary receipts representing securities in its underlying index. The index consists of stocks from the following 10 developed market countries: Austria; Belgium; Finland; France; Germany; Ireland; Italy; the Netherlands; Portugal; and Spain.
